parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Shifter Position Switch/Parking Lever Switch
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter position switch/parking lever switch can cause the vehicle's electrical system to remain active even when the engine is turned off, leading to battery drain and potentially leaving the driver stranded. This can also compromise vehicle safety and security.
symptoms: remains on even after the engine is turned off; the vehicle does not recognize that it is in park; the vehicle cannot be locked; the battery drains quickly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, jerk, or hesitate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the transmission slips or hesitates to engage
the traction control system and tire pressure monitoring lights come on
and the check engine light flashes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The gate shifter issue can cause the vehicle to not turn off when placed in park, leading to battery drain and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle does not turn off when placed in park
and the alarm beeps when the door is opened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the rear brakes can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Grinding or screeching noise when braking
